sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Browser
    participant Django as Django (views.py)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant S3 as S3 / RustFS
    participant Celery as Celery Worker
    participant Doit as doit + papermill
    participant Score as predict_02_score.ipynb

    User->>Browser: Enter income, age, credit_score, employment_years
    Browser->>Django: POST /flows/predict/
    Django->>Django: Validate form inputs
    Django->>S3: Write 1-row CSV → raw/flows/predictions/{run_id}/input.csv
    Django->>DB: Create FlowExecution (flow_name=predict_pipeline, status=PENDING)
    Django->>Celery: run_prediction_task.delay(run_id, s3_path, ...)
    Django-->>Browser: 200 + HTMX poll trigger (prediction_running partial)

    loop Poll every 2s until terminal status
        Browser->>Django: GET /flows/{run_id}/prediction-status/
        Django->>DB: Read FlowExecution.status
        Django-->>Browser: HTMX partial (spinner or result)
    end

    Celery->>DB: Update status → RUNNING
    Celery->>Doit: subprocess doit predict_pipeline (PIPELINE_PARAMS env)

    Doit->>S3: papermill predict_01_ingest.ipynb
    Note over Doit,S3: Reads CSV from S3, writes prediction_input.parquet

    Doit->>Score: papermill predict_02_score.ipynb
    Score->>Score: Compute weighted score<br/>(40% credit_score, 30% income,<br/>20% employment, 10% age)
    Score->>Score: Classify: Approved / Review / Declined
    Score->>S3: Write prediction_result.json
    Score-->>Doit: JSON output (score, classification, confidence)

    Doit-->>Celery: Exit 0 + stdout with result JSON
    Celery->>DB: Update FlowExecution<br/>(status=COMPLETED, parameters.score,<br/>parameters.classification, parameters.confidence)

    Browser->>Django: GET /flows/{run_id}/prediction-status/
    Django->>DB: Read FlowExecution.parameters
    Django-->>Browser: HTMX partial (prediction_result: score + classification badge)
